main event: Unidentified flying object observed on radar at Keflavik, Iceland in March 1952.
interesting points: The object exhibited high angular velocity,The object was tracked on radar but no visual contact was made due to poor weather conditions,The object was reported to have passed at a speed much faster than F-86s,The incident involved multiple USAF personnel making observations,The radar readings indicated the object had an estimated altitude of 2,500 feet.
witness description: U.S. Air Force personnel including Captain Frank Schreiber and Master Sergeant John W. Kelly
